For Task 4 I developed a better understanding of professional communication through e-mail etiquette and responsible social media practices. I composed two emails, both of a formal nature. The first was asking a professor for an extension on an assignment, and the second was enquiring about a possible summer internship. While constructing these emails I tried to be clear with my subject matter, courteous in tone, well-structured and formal in the sign-off of the message.
 I composed a do and do-not list to raise awareness among students about appropriate use of social media. One example of when a breakdown in communication due to lack of digital understanding can create issues is when a student writes an overly casual e-mail to a professor, which can then cause confusion or prevent the student's message from being received effectively. This can be resolved by having the necessary communication etiquette skills.
